content.raw:
@caguero , @andres_fortier this is a big improvement. Here are the old results just to compare:

| Process            | Darpa Example | 10 km sq City |
|--------------------|---------------|---------------|
| RNDF parsing       | 3.05991s      | 189.985s      |
| Messages to Gazebo | 0.0726194s    | 3.65402s      |

Now, I get:

| Process            | Darpa Example | 10 km sq City |
|--------------------|---------------|---------------|
| RNDF parsing       | 0.0143599s    | 0.707127s     |
| Messages to Gazebo | 0.0323384s    | 4.06457s      |

So we are getting an improvement of 213 times for the Darpa sample and 269 for the 10KM sq city.
